{
  "texts": [
    "These systems operate like Kahneman's \"System 1\" thinking-fast, intuitive, but limited to single-pass responses without the ability to reflect or revise (Kahneman, 2011).",
    "Reasoning models, introduced in September 2024, bring \"System 2\" capabilities-deliberate, step-by-step problem solving that can perform complex mathematical derivations and logical analysis.",
    "These models can now solve multi-step problems that consistently challenged earlier systems, from deriving optimal control conditions to implementing sophisticated numerical methods.",
    "The ability to \"think\" through problems systematically has opened new possibilities for theoretical economic work.",
    "Korinek (2024) provides a guide to how these capabilities can benefit economic research."
  ]
}